28 "§ 77-89.2. Creation of Commission authorized.
29 (a) The counties of Catawba, Iredell, Lincoln, and Mecklenburg are hereby authorized
30 participating local governments may by joint resolution to create the Lake Norman Marine
31 Commission. Upon its creation creation, the Commission shall enjoy the powers and have the
32 duties has the powers, duties, and responsibilities conferred upon it by the joint resolution, subject
33 to the provisions of this Act. Article. The provisions of any joint resolution may be modified,
34 amended, or rescinded by a subsequent joint resolution. The purpose of the Lake Norman Marine
35 Commission is to ensure the coordinated governance applicable to Lake Norman and its shoreline
36 area concerning all matters related to public recreation and water quality and safety.
37 (b) A county participating local government may unilaterally withdraw from
38 participation as required by any joint resolution or the provisions of this Act, Article, once the
39 Commission has been created, and any county participating local government may unilaterally
40 withdraw from said commission at the end of any budget period. the Commission by resolution
41 of its board upon the conclusion of the informal settlement discussion provided in subsection
42 (b1) of this section, not to exceed 90 days after the participating local government delivers to the
43 Commission its notice of intent to withdraw.
44 (b1) Upon providing the Commission with notice of intent to withdraw, the participating
45 local government and the Commission shall jointly appoint a mediation officer. The mediation
46 officer shall make a reasonable effort to initiate settlement discussions between the participating
47 local government and all other interested parties.
48 (c) Upon withdrawing from the Commission, a local government is no longer obligated
49 to continue any financial or in-kind support of the Commission. By joint resolution of the
50 participating local governments, presented to and approved by the Commission, an eligible local
51 government may rejoin the Commission as a participating local government.
