10 "§ 77-89.3. Terms of members.Membership; terms of office; eligibility for appointment.
11 (a) Upon its creation, the Commission shall have has a governing board of five
12 commissioners. Except as otherwise provided for the first five-year period, each commissioner
13 shall serve a five-year term, with commissioners to serve overlapping terms so that one
14 commissioner appointment is made each year. Upon creation of the Commission, the board of
15 Catawba County shall appoint two commissioners and the boards of the other three counties shall
16 appoint one each. These initial appointees shall serve until September 30 following their
17 appointment. Thereafter, appointments shall be made each October 1 by the respective boards of
18 the four counties as follows:comprised of members appointed in accordance with subsections (b)
19 and (c) of this section.
20 (1) First year: Commissioner from Catawba, one-year term; commissioner from
21 Iredell, two-year term; commissioner from Lincoln, three-year term;
22 commissioner from Mecklenburg, four-year term; commissioner from
23 Catawba, five-year term.
24 (2) Second year: Commissioner from Iredell, five-year term.
25 (3) Third year: Commissioner from Lincoln, five-year term.
26 (4) Fourth year: Commissioner from Mecklenburg, five-year term.
27 (5) Fifth year: Commissioner from Catawba, five-year term.
28 (6) Sixth and succeeding years: appointments for five-year terms in rotation by
29 county in the order set out above.
30 (b) For the initial appointments, each participating local government shall appoint one
31 commissioner to serve a four-year term and a second commissioner to serve a five-year term.
32 Except as otherwise provided for the initial appointments, each commissioner shall serve a
33 five-year term.
34 (c) Those commissioners appointed by participating local governments in accordance
35 with subsection (b) of this section shall appoint one commissioner to a five-year term who shall
36 serve a one-year term as chair of the Commission. Each succeeding four years, the Commission
37 shall elect a new chair from the current commissioners to serve a one-year term. At the end of
38 each fourth year, the commissioners appointed by participating local governments in accordance
39 with subsection (b) of this section shall repeat the process of electing a chair as provided in this
40 subsection.
41 (d) Participating local governments shall appoint individuals who possess one or more of
42 the following qualifications:
43 (1) Has a primary residence adjoining Lake Norman.
44 (2) Has knowledge of boater safety protocols for all types of vessels.
45 (3) Has knowledge of water quality and aquatic vegetation management.
46 (4) Has experience in law enforcement.
47 (5) Has experience in public recreation management.
48 (6) Has experience in wildlife resources management.
49 (e) No more than thirty-five percent (35%) of the commissioners serving at any given
50 time may reside in the same county.
