33 SECTION 1.(d) Article 6B of Chapter 77 of the General Statutes, as enacted by
34 subsection (a) of this section and amended by subsections (b) and (c) of this section, is amended
35 by adding a new section to read:
36 "§ 77-89.9. Fees.
37 (a) Except as limited by any other provisions of State or federal law, the Commission
38 may assess fees related to all of the following:
39 (1) Participation in education, training, or certification services provided by the
40 Commission.
41 (2) Use of facilities owned or operated by the Commission.
42 (3) Application for a permit administered by the Commission to regulate
43 privileged or special uses of Lake Norman and its shoreline area.
44 (b) In setting fee amounts to be charged for activities provided in subsection (a) of this
45 section, the Commission shall not do any of the following:
46 (1) Set a fee in an excessive amount that that is neither reasonable nor customary
47 for the services and privileges provided by the Commission.
48 (2) Set a fee in an amount that exceeds the Commission's actual costs for the
49 service provided.
50 (3) Charge fees for general access to Lake Norman or its shoreline area.
51 (4) Discriminate on the basis of race, color, sex, religious creed, or national origin.
