4 SECTION 4.(a) Any joint resolution adopted by the four counties pursuant to
5 Chapter 1089 of the 1969 Session Laws, that is in effect immediately prior to the effective date
6 of this act, shall expire upon the adoption of a subsequent joint resolution by the participating
7 local governments consistent with the provisions of this act or September 30, 2025, whichever is
8 earlier.
9 SECTION 4.(b) The terms of the commissioners currently appointed to the
10 governing board of the Lake Norman Marine Commission shall expire on September 30, 2025.
11 SECTION 5. Upon the Lake Norman Marine Commission being reconstituted
12 pursuant to a joint resolution adopted by the participating local governments, all new
13 appointments to the governing board of the Lake Norman Marine Commission will be effective
14 on October 1, 2025.
15 SECTION 6. All rules, regulations, and decisions made by the predecessor Lake
16 Norman Marine Commission, reconstituted in accordance with this act, shall remain in full force
17 and effect until and unless duly modified by the successor entity.
18 SECTION 7. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
19 law.
